    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ⚙️ Setup Required\n\n1. GitHub Personal Access Token\n   → github.com/settings/tokens\n   → Scopes: repo, read:user\n\n2. Gemini API Key\n   → aistudio.google.com\n   → Free tier is enough\n\n3. Gmail OAuth2\n   → Connect your Google account\n   → Allow n8n permissions",
        "height": 304,
        "width": 560,
        "color": 4
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        128,
        -320
      ],
      "id": "26d374b5-872b-4739-93ac-f0499e7b5ac8",
      "name": "Sticky Note1"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🔄 Workflow Steps\n\n1. WEBHOOK TRIGGER\n   Receives a POST request with\n   {\"repo\": \"owner/repo-name\"}\n\n2. GITHUB API\n   Fetches up to 30 open issues + PRs\n   from the specified repository\n\n3. CODE NODE\n   Formats each item: number, type,\n   labels, title, and body preview\n\n4. GEMINI AI\n   Prioritizes items into:\n   🔴 Critical / 🟡 Important\n   🟢 Features / ⚪ Maintenance\n\n5. GMAIL\n   Sends the full report to your inbox",
        "height": 624,
        "width": 352,
        "color": 5
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -240,
        -320
      ],
      "id": "24ada078-a47d-42a9-9be7-2bf2bd839125",
      "name": "Sticky Note2"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🚀 How to Use\n\nSend a POST request from your terminal:\n\ncurl -X POST YOUR_WEBHOOK_URL \\\n-H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n-d '{\"repo\": \"activepieces/activepieces\"}'\n\nReplace YOUR_WEBHOOK_URL with the\nproduction URL from the Webhook node.\n\nWorks with ANY public GitHub repo!\nTry: \"vercel/next.js\" or \"nestjs/nest\"",
        "height": 304,
